Available for deployment!

Despite everything our dedicated team of tiny engineeres continues to push forward in the field of tiny military transportation. Our latest offering is the fresh addition of two self-propelled artillery systems. These fully enclosed machines are perfect for any army - whether you desire to lob shells from afar or blast enemy strogpoints at point blank range.

This kit includes all the necessary parts you need to add either long ranged SPG or a powerful Assault Cannon to your force. Included a host of optional accessories.

Furthermore all roof hatches are rendered fully operational so that you can always wave at your comrades while the crew is busy shelling someone kilometers afar.

This vehicle is perfect for any games involving tiny tanks or robots in 6 to 8mm scale.

Rumbling forward on heavy tracks, the tanks of the Imperial Army are capable of decimating enemy forces with overwhelming firepower. The versatile main battle tank hull is capable of being adapted to feature a wide range of alternate patterns - including devastating artillery.

This set of 79 STLS, and features the heavy 'Bombardier' tank, the long range 'Basil' tank, and the medium 'Euryale' tank, each with variants with and without bulldozer blade, and variants with holes onto which plastic open hatches from comparable plastic tank kits are compatible. There are also additional hull variants, of each tank, including an Imperial Army Bombardier tank, and hulls with extra armour, plus some kit form Bombardiers. Also included are a range of an optional details, including rear-mounted mounted dozer blade (enabling the artillery to 'dig in' prior to firing), rear mounted trailers, support struts, and shells that can be used to add features to any bases you wish to mount the tanks on.

This set has been made to be compatible with 8mm scale main line battle tanks of the Imperial Army in a recently released 8mm grim-dark future wargame.

Please see my other items for a free sample of this set, and a range of other 8mm scale and other wargames and hobby models. I am an enthusiastic amateur designer, self and video-tutorial taught, so am always open to constructive feedback.

Please consider liking the design and posting a make.

The All-Purpose Carrier lives up to its name as a rugged and dependable platform that has been adapted to almost every role on & off the battlefield.

This all-in-one package of M'khand-pattern All-Purpose Carrier parts allows you to build your ideal APC-based vehicle to your exact needs. Contains all previously released APC-chassis related files***, both free and paid, adapted to 1:300 scale for mass-scale wargames.

Turrets and middles have 2.5x1.25mm holes for magnets. Compatible with all epic scale M'khand-pattern APC & Lemoine Russel turrets.

To use meshmixer builder, open with meshmixer (a free program from autodesk) and ctrl-click in the object browser the items you wish to have as one piece. Then go to File and Export. Your merged piece is ready for repair and slicing.

Alternatively, individual part stls can be assembled in 3Dbuilder or another program of your choice where they should snap together.

***Non-IFV turrets, Christie suspension sides and artillery cannons for unarmoured hulls not included***

2022-12-30: Added track guards to the builder.

2022-12-30: Added new options for sponson and hull-mounted weapons.

2024-01-23: Added missing armoured artillery mounts and cannons.

2024-08-20: Renamed the parts to be much easier to read. Added new turret parts, new SPG, SPM, and scout tank middles, and wheeled sides (wheels themselves should be printed separately)

2024-09-26: Added hatches for side weapon arrays
